3.  On firegrate in a barbecue, with a lid, ignite 50-60 charcoal briquettes.  When briquettes are dotted with ash, in about 30 minutes, spread them into a single layer; scatter 10-12 more briquettes over coals.  Set grill 5-6" above coals.  Lift meat onto grill; reserve marinade.  Put lid on barbecue and open vents.

